Lasgalen, Sixteenth Autumn Initiate of Tunare <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urobingoodfellow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Robin Goodfellow</A> at: 12/20/01 2:32:36 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukaeliic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaeliic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 75<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/20/01 2:52:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=933.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I think...</span><hr size=1> Read Verant's rules...there are NO camps...people just allow other players to have camps out of curtosy.  The fact is, who gets agro first gets the right to kill the mob first.  This is the only thing that the guides will go by..who had agro first.  This is usually seen by the NPC saying something along the lines of &quot;woodelves like you make me sick&quot;, etc...<br>
<br>
If you walk into a camp and see someone just standing there, looking dumb at the mob, then go ahead and attack it....the Guides will be on your side when the petition goes through, not that I am a KSer or anything, but someone farming a mob over and over again tends to get on one's nerves.  I do respect camps, but I also understand that if I don't have my &quot;camped&quot; mob engaged when someone come strutting by, they have the right (as much as I would hate it) to come and take the mob while I fight with all the placeholders, etc.  'Tis Verant's rule.<br>
<br>
