A. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ulexxiclockwork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lexxi Clockwork</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/20/01 3:54:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=933.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I think...</span><hr size=1>      I have to say that if it is the same guy there time after time and he cannot even use the item he is not camping it, he is farming it. I can see getting help, but I believe the person that will be using the item should hold the spot, not an alt or a higher level member that cannot even use it. I am very proud of my testament, I stayed and watched for Dylin for over 6 hours. The smugglers killed me before I killed him, but I managed to get back on and kill Dylin before any oppurtunists could (and they tried but he was in the water and I got to him first). It took me a week for my turn, but I stayed and got him, but I will never hold the spot for someone else. I will help them, but I will not hold the spot.<br>
