<br>
Dhugal <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urobingoodfellow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Robin Goodfellow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/20/01 4:26:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=933.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I think...</span><hr size=1> I tried to speak to them through a translator today (Thank you, Pulin).<br>
<br>
I asked why the monk, Shewina, was still there.  She admitted that she was getting it &quot;for her family&quot; (read: farming it for her guild).  I asked for an apology and a shot at the camp, or my page back.<br>
<br>
Then she and her guildmembers, Annarose and Bogglebee, got very rude, accused me of KSing Dyllin last night (I did not), and that I had to sit there for six hours if I wanted my shot at the camp.  Otherwise, it was theirs.<br>
<br>
Also, Annarose tried to cast various spells on me--presumably Snare and Grasping Roots or the like.  She successfully cast Harmony on me.<br>
<br>
Two other guildmembers, Dyren and Wyam, were there as well.<br>
<br>
I just want a shot at this and an apology from them for what was clearly a deception.  I thought this woman was a druid, had camped there for six hours, and was frustrated that I got it without having to wait.  It turns out she's just farming it for her guild, so they don't have to wait six hours.  Shame on them.  Shame on all of them.  If I'd known this from the beginning, I would most definitely have not given up that page.<br>
<br>
And now, on top of all that, they accuse me of being a Kill-Stealer.<br>
<br>
What a bunch of ungrateful louts.<br>
<br>
Yes, I'd like to hear their defense of this behavior.<br>
<br>
If someone would post the link to their website, I'd appreciate that.  Maybe this can be worked out through e-mail.  I really just want a shot at the camp and an apology, or my page back.  That's all.  I don't intend to drag their names through the mud, because I don't know any of these people and have never had any prior encounters with them, good or bad.<br>
<br>
Lasgalen<br>
<br>
(And if they thought I was KSing before...  just wait.) <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urobingoodfellow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Robin Goodfellow</A> at: 12/20/01 4:31:47 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usoneldarblackrose.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Soneldar Blackrose</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 70<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/20/01 4:40:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=933.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I think...</span><hr size=1> At this point, I would bring Verant into this.  It is obvious that Oaken no longer is honor bound and instead has to rely on zombies for the good equipment.  On top of that, they make accusations that do not hold even a drop of water.  I say pull PnP on their arses and royally screw them.  Screw them over, and do it well, my friend.   <p>Soneldar Blackrose
<br>Wood Elvian Druid of the 23rd Season<br><i>"Fear me o daemon, for I am the Blackrose!  I shall be the wings that carry you to your death!"</i><br>-Warcry of the Blackrose</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/unobbwin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nobbwin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/20/01 4:58:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=933.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I think...</span><hr size=1> I'm currently a member of the Oaken. Not a very active one, I'm afraid, but they have a web site hosted by Guildsay, and most of the officer's email addies are there.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.guildsay.com/guilds/view_guild.php?guild=310">www.guildsay.com/guilds/v...?guild=310</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
I&quot;ve also posted my thoughts on our private message board. I&quot;ve grouped occasionally with the folks named in this thread, and am surprised to hear this story. I hope it isn't as bad as it sounds, and I have asked any officer to come here and state a case.<br>
<br>
